          <p>
            Steve Paull brings over 25 years of experience at the intersection of business strategy, technology, and organizational transformation. His career spans management consulting, enterprise technology leadership, and executive roles at Fortune 500 companies — giving him a unique perspective that bridges boardroom strategy with operational execution.
          </p>
          <p>
            Most recently, Steve served as <strong>Senior Vice President of Enterprise Applications at Victoria's Secret & Co.</strong>, where he led enterprise application strategy and delivery across the organization. Prior to that, he held Vice President roles in Data Services, Application Services, and Enterprise HR Systems at L Brands.
          </p>
          <p>
            Steve's consulting roots run deep. As a <strong>Partner and Senior Vice President of Consulting Services at Navigator Management Partners</strong>, he was the firm's first employee and helped grow the company to 140 employees and $40 million in annual revenue over a 15-year tenure. He served as the Retail Industry Lead, Business Process Design and HR Technology Capability Lead, and led large enterprise resource planning implementations across Higher Education, Retail, and Healthcare industries.
          </p>
          <p>
            His career began at <strong>Accenture</strong>, and includes a role as Senior Systems Integrator at <strong>The Wendy's Company</strong>, grounding him in hands-on technology delivery from day one.
          </p>
